{
  "text": "In our study we assess impacts-driven vulnerability, where vulnerability is defined in direct proportion to the magnitude of hydrological change. However, we note that recent work on the human dimensions of climate change have demonstrated that vulnerability emerges from the interaction of both environmental and social dynamics in specific contexts [CITATION_1] 70 .",
  "correct_citation": {
